I came in here at least twice a week for the past two weeks to get 2 cinnamon buns. I pay $4.85, but today I paid $6.35. I didn’t pay attention until I looked at my receipt. When I approached the manager she just had a attitude. When I tried to take one cinnamon back, she just scrunched her face up and said I already ate the other. Me eating one does not matter because in food service you’re not supposed to take back food that’s already handed out which seemed like she was eager to do if I wouldn’t have ate one. This lady has terrible customer service, because anywhere else the customer is always right. Not only that, but if I’m dissatisfied with something you can either give me my money back, or change it to something else. She did not offer anything but a nasty attitude. I will not be coming back here.

Stopped in for some hot coffee.  The staff were very friendly and active. The place was clean and roomy.  The decor seemed a little off - like two competing design concepts were at play rather than one fluid interior. Am I modern? Am I retro? Am I an old fashioned clubhouse lounge? Am I a neighborhood corner shop? Am I a corporate ditto box?  The coffee was indeed hot, and for two bucks I can't complain.  The wifi was free, easy to connect, and reliable.

Lets start with the good points.  The place was clean, the people were smiling.  All done. My wife and I ordered the mac and cheese with a Caesar and a meatball panini with side salad.  the server delivered my wife's meal and got confused and walked around the place for 10 minutes before we were able to flag her down to confirm that the plate she held was mine.  The mac and cheese tasted like velveeta and the meatball panini was bland and dry on the inside.  all you tasted was butter.   not worth the price charged.  we will not be going back anytime soon.
